Edwina Bolosha from Tumahole had been last seen at home last weekend and was reported missing days later. Twitter/SAPS JOHANNESBURG - The body of a 14-year-old girl has been found under a pile of rocks in the Free State. Edwina Bolosha from Tumahole had been last seen at home last weekend and was reported missing days later. Her uncle last saw her when she left home for a sleepover at a friend's place. The teen's 24-year-old boyfriend has been taken in for questioning. Police are urging people to report missing children as soon as possible.